In this article, President Donald Trump issues a proclamation declaring October 2, 2020, as National Manufacturing Day. He highlights the importance of American manufacturing for the country's economic prosperity and national security. Trump mentions his efforts to support American manufacturers, such as signing the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act and renegotiating trade deals. He also emphasizes the role of manufacturing in responding to the coronavirus pandemic, with American manufacturers producing essential goods and medical supplies. Trump expresses optimism for the future of American manufacturing and calls upon all Americans to celebrate and support the industry.